description: Bright light filters in from the north, its steady glow clearly illuminating the cobblestones of the floor, ceiling, and walls, while also casting the southern end in shadows.  Not a stitch of debris, dust, dirt, or cobwebs litters the floors or clogs the corners and the scent of fresh water mixes heavily with lavender in this section of the passage.
title: [Mist Harbor Proper, Sewers]
